            "size": 1355,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_014ZhnqdZAsA1RxgjSdJ77iN\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I appreciate that detail—the vetting process is important context for how your platform works. But I need to redirect slightly: **who is your primary customer?** Are you selling to podcast hosts, or to guests, or both equally?\\n\\nLet me ask more directly:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"When you think about who's paying for Friend of the Pod—is it primarily podcast hosts looking for guests? Or are you going after both sides? And what's the main pain point you're solving for them?\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Podcast hosts who are tired of spending hours vetting random guest pitches and want a curated, pre-vetted pool\\\",\\n    \\\"Busy show producers who need a faster way to fill their guest slots without sacrificing quality\\\",\\n    \\\"Established podcasts scaling from 1-2 episodes per week to daily content\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"This helps us understand who we're writing the landing page copy for.\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3002,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":227,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
