            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it! Now let's talk about your **solution** — how does Friend of the Pod actually solve the pain points for your users?\\n\\nIn other words:\\n- **For hosts:** What's the step-by-step experience? How does the AI matching work? What do they get?\\n- **For guests:** How do they benefit? What's easy about it?\\n\\nThink about the tangible outcomes: faster bookings, better guest quality, more exposure, etc.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Now let's talk about your solution — how does Friend of the Pod actually solve the pain points for your users? For hosts: What's the step-by-step experience? How does the AI matching work? What do they get? For guests: How do they benefit? What's easy about it? Think about the tangible outcomes: faster bookings, better guest quality, more exposure, etc.\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect! Now let's move to **social proof**. \\n\\nThis is about building credibility on your landing page. Social proof can be:\\n- **Testimonials** from early users (hosts or guests who've had success)\\n- **Your founder story** — why you're the right person to build this\\n- **Your background/expertise** — podcast industry experience, AI/tech chops, etc.\\n- **Early traction** — number of matches made, podcasts using the platform, etc.\\n- **Press mentions** or industry recognition\\n\\nWhat social proof do you have, or what's your angle for building trust with visitors?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Now let's move to social proof. This is about building credibility on your landing page. Social proof can be: testimonials from early users (hosts or guests who've had success), your founder story — why you're the right person to build this, your background/expertise — podcast industry experience, AI/tech chops, etc., or early traction — number of matches made, podcasts using the platform, etc. What social proof do you have, or what's your angle for building trust with visitors?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"<background>\\n  The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n      We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n</background>\\n\\n<where_we_are>\\n  Right now, we're in the brainstorming phase. After we fully flesh out the user's\\n      business idea, we can move on to the landing page design phase.\\n</where_we_are>\\n\\n<context>\\n  The user skipped 3 questions during the brainstorm.\\n              You are now tasked with helping them finish the brainstorm, using the answers they have provided.\\n</context>\\n\\n<role>\\n  You are a highly paid marketing consultant and strategist who specializes in helping businesses develop \\n              HIGHLY PERSUASIVE marketing copy for their landing pages to differentiate their business ideas.\\n</role>\\n\\n<task>\\n  Create plausible answers for the skipped topics based on the answers the user has provided.\\n\\n              Do not invent answers or make things up. Use the information provided to create realistic answers.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\nThe target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\n\\nHow does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\n\\nSocial proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\n          TOPIC: Target Audience\\n\\nThe user needs help describing who their ideal customer is and what problems they face.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- Break this into 3-4 clear sub-questions\\n- Sub-questions should build logically: WHO → PROBLEMS → GOALS → (optionally) WHY EXISTING SOLUTIONS FAIL\\n- Each sub-question should have a bold header and bracketed guidance\\n- Help them get specific about demographics AND psychographics\\n- Emphasize connecting problems to goals (they're two sides of same coin)\\n\\nSUB-QUESTIONS TO INCLUDE:\\n\\n1. **Who are they?** - Demographics, role, life context\\n2. **What problems do they face?** - Pain points, frustrations, obstacles\\n3. **What are they trying to achieve?** - Goals, desired outcomes, aspirations\\n4. (Optional) **Why don't current solutions work?** - Gap in market\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Should paint a vivid picture of a real person\\n- Must show clear connection between their problems and goals\\n- Problems should be specific, not generic (\\\"overwhelmed by too much to do\\\")\\n- Should help them see the emotional dimension, not just functional\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"Busy professionals who want to save time\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"Marketing managers at 10-50 person SaaS companies who are stretched thin managing multiple channels, feel guilty about inconsistent posting, and want to build thought leadership but can't justify hiring a full-time content person.\\\"\\n\\n\\nTOPIC: How Your Product Solves the Problem\\n\\nThe user needs help explaining how their product addresses their audience's pain points.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- Structure as a clear problem → solution → outcome flow\\n- Provide 3 building-block questions that connect cause and effect\\n- Emphasize CONNECTING back to pain points they mentioned earlier\\n- Help them focus on the mechanism and transformation, not feature lists\\n- The outcome should be tangible and specific\\n\\nFRAMEWORK STRUCTURE:\\n\\n1. **What specific problem does it solve?** - Direct reference to audience pain points\\n2. **How does it work?** - Brief mechanism or approach (not feature list)\\n3. **What outcome do customers get?** - The transformation or result\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Must show clear problem → solution → outcome causality\\n- Should reference specific pain points (time, stress, money, etc.)\\n- Outcome should be measurable or observable\\n- Avoid feature lists - focus on approach and benefit\\n- Should show WHY this solution is better, not just WHAT it does\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"Our app has AI and analytics to help you work better\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"Solves the problem of scattered project updates by automatically aggregating status from Slack, email, and project tools into one daily digest, so managers get full visibility without having to chase down team members - saving 5+ hours of meetings per week.\\\"\\n\\n\\nTOPIC: Social Proof and Credibility\\n\\nThe user needs help identifying what credibility indicators or proof points they can include.\\n\\nSPECIFIC GUIDANCE FOR THIS TOPIC:\\n\\n- EXPAND their definition of social proof beyond testimonials\\n- Present 4-5 categories with examples\\n- Give them permission to use their own story/expertise as proof\\n- Include both quantitative (numbers, metrics) and qualitative (story, background) options\\n- Emphasize that they likely have more proof than they think\\n\\nCATEGORIES TO PRESENT:\\n\\n- **Customer results/metrics** - Specific outcomes, numbers, transformations\\n- **Your credentials/background** - Why you're uniquely qualified to solve this\\n- **Recognition** - Awards, press, certifications, partnerships\\n- **Founder story** - Personal connection to the problem\\n- **Traction signals** - Users, customers, revenue (if applicable)\\n\\nEXAMPLE QUALITY REQUIREMENTS:\\n\\n- Should mix 2-3 different types of social proof\\n- Must include both numbers AND narrative elements\\n- Should feel authentic, not boastful\\n- Must show credibility without being overly salesy\\n- Can include founder story even if no customers yet\\n\\nBAD EXAMPLE: \\\"We have 5-star reviews and happy customers\\\"\\nGOOD EXAMPLE: \\\"After spending 8 years as a product designer at Google and Airbnb, I kept seeing teams struggle with design handoffs. Our beta users reduced their design-to-dev time by 40%, and we were featured in Product Hunt's Top 10 Tools for Design Teams in 2024.\\\"\\n<task>\\n  Provide a clear, fill-in-the-blank template that helps them articulate their answer with specificity and clarity.\\n</task>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  Do not output any text. Call the save_answers tool with the answers you have created for the skipped topics.\\n</output_format_rules>\"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 3025,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 3025,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01WqSRaKbUhmMtzYzdceQzC9\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DxABydFP5vrZ9f2SD7PFmu\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"**Podcast hosts** at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who are actively producing content but struggle with guest sourcing. They face the pain of spending 5-10+ hours per episode manually searching for guests through email outreach, social media, and industry networks—often with low response rates and mismatched fits. Their goal is to fill their guest slots quickly with high-quality, relevant guests who will bring value to their audience and boost episode quality. Current solutions (email lists, manual networking, generic guest databases) are time-consuming, hit-or-miss, and don't scale. They want a fast, intelligent way to find the right guests so they can focus on content creation instead of sourcing.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the guest sourcing bottleneck by automating the matching process. **For hosts:** Instead of spending hours manually searching, they input their podcast details, audience, and ideal guest profile. The AI-powered platform instantly filters through thousands of potential guests and surfaces the best matches in minutes—ranked by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Hosts get a curated list of pre-qualified guests ready to pitch, cutting sourcing time from hours to minutes and dramatically increasing booking success rates. **For guests:** They create a profile once, get discovered by hosts actively looking for their expertise, and gain exposure to new audiences without having to pitch themselves repeatedly. The outcome: hosts book better guests faster, guests get more speaking opportunities, and both sides save significant time and effort.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"**Founder expertise:** Built by someone deeply embedded in the podcast ecosystem with [X years] of experience in [podcasting/audio/tech], giving credibility to understanding both host and guest pain points. **Early traction:** [Number] of successful matches made, [number] of podcasts using the platform, demonstrating real market validation. **Guest testimonials:** Quotes from hosts who've reduced their sourcing time by [X%] and guests who've landed speaking opportunities they wouldn't have found otherwise. **Problem validation:** The 'needle in a haystack' problem is real—hosts consistently cite guest sourcing as their #1 time drain, making this a proven pain point worth solving. **AI credibility:** Leveraging AI-powered matching positions the platform as a modern, intelligent solution vs. outdated manual methods.\"}]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3168,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":609,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
          },
