            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"description\":\"\\n        Save answers to the brainstorming session.\\n        Call this when the user has answered one or more of the remaining topics.\\n\\n        If the user answered the question themselves: Do not provide any arguments.\\n        If you are answering SKIPPED questions for the user, provide answers in your\\n        own words\\n    \",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"answers\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"idea\",\"audience\",\"solution\",\"socialProof\",\"lookAndFeel\"]},\"answer\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"answer\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"finishedTool\",\"description\":\"Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{},\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}},{\"name\":\"query_uploads\",\"description\":\"Query the user's uploaded images for this project.\\nUse this tool when the user mentions images they've uploaded previously but aren't\\nattached to the current message. For example:\\n- \\\"Use the product photos I uploaded earlier\\\"\\n- \\\"Can you see my recent image uploads?\\\"\\n- \\\"Use the logo I uploaded\\\"\\n\\nReturns a list of uploaded images with their URLs and metadata.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query_type\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"enum\":[\"recent\",\"logos\",\"all\"],\"description\":\"Type of images to query: 'recent' for most recent product images, 'logos' for logo images only, 'all' for all images\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of images to return. Defaults to 10.\"}},\"required\":[\"query_type\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"What is your business?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\n            We solve the \\\"needle in a haystack\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Got it! Now let's talk about your **solution** — how does Friend of the Pod actually solve the pain points for your users?\\n\\nIn other words:\\n- **For hosts:** What's the step-by-step experience? How does the AI matching work? What do they get?\\n- **For guests:** How do they benefit? What's easy about it?\\n\\nThink about the tangible outcomes: faster bookings, better guest quality, more exposure, etc.\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Now let's talk about your solution — how does Friend of the Pod actually solve the pain points for your users? For hosts: What's the step-by-step experience? How does the AI matching work? What do they get? For guests: How do they benefit? What's easy about it? Think about the tangible outcomes: faster bookings, better guest quality, more exposure, etc.\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Perfect! Now let's move to **social proof**. \\n\\nThis is about building credibility on your landing page. Social proof can be:\\n- **Testimonials** from early users (hosts or guests who've had success)\\n- **Your founder story** — why you're the right person to build this\\n- **Your background/expertise** — podcast industry experience, AI/tech chops, etc.\\n- **Early traction** — number of matches made, podcasts using the platform, etc.\\n- **Press mentions** or industry recognition\\n\\nWhat social proof do you have, or what's your angle for building trust with visitors?\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Now let's move to social proof. This is about building credibility on your landing page. Social proof can be: testimonials from early users (hosts or guests who've had success), your founder story — why you're the right person to build this, your background/expertise — podcast industry experience, AI/tech chops, etc., or early traction — number of matches made, podcasts using the platform, etc. What social proof do you have, or what's your angle for building trust with visitors?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Skip\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DxABydFP5vrZ9f2SD7PFmu\",\"name\":\"save_answers\",\"input\":{\"answers\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"answer\":\"**Podcast hosts** at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who are actively producing content but struggle with guest sourcing. They face the pain of spending 5-10+ hours per episode manually searching for guests through email outreach, social media, and industry networks—often with low response rates and mismatched fits. Their goal is to fill their guest slots quickly with high-quality, relevant guests who will bring value to their audience and boost episode quality. Current solutions (email lists, manual networking, generic guest databases) are time-consuming, hit-or-miss, and don't scale. They want a fast, intelligent way to find the right guests so they can focus on content creation instead of sourcing.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"answer\":\"Friend of the Pod solves the guest sourcing bottleneck by automating the matching process. **For hosts:** Instead of spending hours manually searching, they input their podcast details, audience, and ideal guest profile. The AI-powered platform instantly filters through thousands of potential guests and surfaces the best matches in minutes—ranked by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Hosts get a curated list of pre-qualified guests ready to pitch, cutting sourcing time from hours to minutes and dramatically increasing booking success rates. **For guests:** They create a profile once, get discovered by hosts actively looking for their expertise, and gain exposure to new audiences without having to pitch themselves repeatedly. The outcome: hosts book better guests faster, guests get more speaking opportunities, and both sides save significant time and effort.\"},{\"topic\":\"socialProof\",\"answer\":\"**Founder expertise:** Built by someone deeply embedded in the podcast ecosystem with [X years] of experience in [podcasting/audio/tech], giving credibility to understanding both host and guest pain points. **Early traction:** [Number] of successful matches made, [number] of podcasts using the platform, demonstrating real market validation. **Guest testimonials:** Quotes from hosts who've reduced their sourcing time by [X%] and guests who've landed speaking opportunities they wouldn't have found otherwise. **Problem validation:** The 'needle in a haystack' problem is real—hosts consistently cite guest sourcing as their #1 time drain, making this a proven pain point worth solving. **AI credibility:** Leveraging AI-powered matching positions the platform as a modern, intelligent solution vs. outdated manual methods.\"}]}}]},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Saving answers...\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DxABydFP5vrZ9f2SD7PFmu\"}]}],\"system\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n        \\n    <background>\\n        The user is creating a new landing page for their business idea.\\n        We are helping them brainstorm and refine their messaging.\\n    </background>\\n    \\n\\n        <where_we_are>\\n            We've successfully FINISHED brainstorming everything we need to create a killer landing page.\\n\\n            Now the user has two options:\\n\\n            1) Personalize the look and feel of their page before we build (optional)\\n            2) Build the landing page (handoff to AI agent)\\n        </where_we_are>\\n\\n        <role>\\n            You are the helpful UI navigator. You will help the user navigate the UI\\n            to either option 1 or option 2.\\n\\n            CRITICAL: If the user says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", or\\n            indicates they are ready to move on, you MUST call the finishedTool immediately.\\n            Do NOT respond with text - just call the tool to redirect them.\\n        </role>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming AND hasn't told you what they want to do yet\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n                - If they have process questions, you don't need to explain the UI options again\\n                - Read the room.\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", etc.\\n                - IMPORTANT: Do NOT respond with text when calling this tool. Just call it.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <available_options>\\n            ### 1. Brand Personalization (OPTIONAL - Left Sidebar)\\n            - Upload logo\\n            - Choose color palette\\n            - Add social links (Twitter, Instagram, LinkedIn, etc.)\\n            - Upload custom images for the page\\n            - The user can do any or all of these steps\\n            - Otherwise, we'll apply smart defaults\\n\\n            ### 2. Build My Site Button\\n            - Ready to generate the landing page whenever they are\\n            - They can click \\\"Build My Site\\\" when they're ready to proceed\\n            - If, if they've indicated that they're finished, you can call the finished tool,\\n              which will redirect them to the website builder. You do not need to reply\\n              to the user in this case.\\n        </available_options>\\n\\n        \\n    <collected_answers>\\n        {\\\"audience\\\":\\\"**Podcast hosts** at independent and mid-sized shows (10K-500K listeners) who are actively producing content but struggle with guest sourcing. They face the pain of spending 5-10+ hours per episode manually searching for guests through email outreach, social media, and industry networks—often with low response rates and mismatched fits. Their goal is to fill their guest slots quickly with high-quality, relevant guests who will bring value to their audience and boost episode quality. Current solutions (email lists, manual networking, generic guest databases) are time-consuming, hit-or-miss, and don't scale. They want a fast, intelligent way to find the right guests so they can focus on content creation instead of sourcing.\\\",\\\"idea\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to match hosts with ideal guests in minutes, rather than hosts spending hours searching manually. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content and guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does this matchmaking at scale.\\\",\\\"socialProof\\\":\\\"**Founder expertise:** Built by someone deeply embedded in the podcast ecosystem with [X years] of experience in [podcasting/audio/tech], giving credibility to understanding both host and guest pain points. **Early traction:** [Number] of successful matches made, [number] of podcasts using the platform, demonstrating real market validation. **Guest testimonials:** Quotes from hosts who've reduced their sourcing time by [X%] and guests who've landed speaking opportunities they wouldn't have found otherwise. **Problem validation:** The 'needle in a haystack' problem is real—hosts consistently cite guest sourcing as their #1 time drain, making this a proven pain point worth solving. **AI credibility:** Leveraging AI-powered matching positions the platform as a modern, intelligent solution vs. outdated manual methods.\\\",\\\"solution\\\":\\\"Friend of the Pod solves the guest sourcing bottleneck by automating the matching process. **For hosts:** Instead of spending hours manually searching, they input their podcast details, audience, and ideal guest profile. The AI-powered platform instantly filters through thousands of potential guests and surfaces the best matches in minutes—ranked by relevance, audience fit, and availability. Hosts get a curated list of pre-qualified guests ready to pitch, cutting sourcing time from hours to minutes and dramatically increasing booking success rates. **For guests:** They create a profile once, get discovered by hosts actively looking for their expertise, and gain exposure to new audiences without having to pitch themselves repeatedly. The outcome: hosts book better guests faster, guests get more speaking opportunities, and both sides save significant time and effort.\\\"}\\n    </collected_answers>\\n    \\n\\n        <communication_approach>\\n            ### ✅ DO:\\n            - Celebrate their accomplishment enthusiastically (if we haven't already)\\n            - Make personalization feel OPTIONAL, not required\\n            - Empower them to choose their own path\\n            - Be brief - they don't need a long explanation\\n            - Create excitement about seeing their page\\n\\n            ## Example Messages\\n\\n            ### First-Time Completion:\\n            json\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for you. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n                \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They Ask What to Do Next:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"Great question! You're all set to build. Here's what you can do:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"If you have brand assets ready (logo, colors, images) - add them in the Brand Personalization panel on the left\\\",\\n                \\\"If you want to see the page first - just click 'Build My Site' and we'll use smart defaults\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Both paths work great. Which feels right to you?\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ### If They're Hesitating:\\n            {\\n            \\\"text\\\": \\\"No pressure at all! Here's the deal:\\\",\\n            \\\"examples\\\": [\\n                \\\"You can build now with our smart defaults and customize later\\\",\\n                \\\"Or you can upload your logo and brand colors first if you have them handy\\\",\\n                \\\"The page will look great either way\\\"\\n            ],\\n            \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Whatever's easier for you is the right choice!\\\"\\n            }\\n\\n            ## Handling Different Scenarios\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Personalize:\\n            \\\"Perfect! Take your time with the Brand Personalization panel. When you're ready, hit 'Build My Site' and I'll create your page with your custom branding!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Wants to Build Immediately:\\n            \\\"Love it! Hit that 'Build My Site' button and let's see what we've got. You can always come back and adjust colors, logos, etc. later.\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Is Unsure:\\n            \\\"Here's my recommendation: If you have your logo and brand colors ready right now, add them. If not, don't worry about it - just build the page and we can customize later. The goal is to get something live!\\\"\\n\\n            ### User Asks \\\"What Do You Recommend?\\\":\\n            \\\"Honestly? If you have your logo file and know your brand colors, it takes 2 minutes to add them and looks great. But if you don't have those handy, just build now. Don't let perfection slow you down!\\\"\\n\\n            ## Key Principles\\n\\n            ### 1. Remove Decision Paralysis\\n            Don't make them overthink. Both options are good.\\n\\n            ### 2. No Wrong Choice\\n            Building without personalization is 100% valid. So is personalizing first.\\n\\n            ### 3. Urgency Without Pressure\\n            Create excitement to see their page, but no obligation to rush.\\n\\n            ### 4. Lower the Stakes\\n            They can always customize later. This isn't permanent.\\n\\n            ## What TO Say\\n\\n            ✅ \\\"You're ready to build whenever you are!\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"Personalization is optional - add what you want, skip what you don't\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"You can always customize later\\\"\\n            ✅ \\\"What feels right to you?\\\"\\n\\n            ## Goal\\n\\n            Get them to either:\\n            1. Add brand personalization (if they have it ready), OR\\n            2. Click \\\"Build My Site\\\"\\n\\n            Without making either feel like the wrong choice. Create excitement and reduce friction.\\n        </communication_approach>\\n\\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 4 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming AND hasn't indicated what they want to do\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - TRIGGER: User says \\\"I'm finished\\\", \\\"let's build\\\", \\\"build my site\\\", etc.\\n                - CRITICAL: Just call the tool. Do NOT respond with text.\\n\\n            4. Query the user's uploaded images\\n                - Use when: The user mentions images they've uploaded previously\\n                - Call the query_uploads tool to fetch their images\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <tools>\\n  <important>\\n    You have 1 tools available:\\n  </important>\\n  <tool>\\n    <name>\\n      finishedTool\\n    </name>\\n    <description>\\n      Indicate that the user is finished and ready to build their landing page.\\n    </description>\\n    <schema>\\n      [object Object]\\n    </schema>\\n  </tool>\\n</tools>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n\\n        <structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"type\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"const\\\":\\\"reply\\\"},\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"type\\\",\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 986,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 986,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01YP5R8oLCkmqLvD6gQM88ip\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"reply\\\",\\n  \\\"text\\\": \\\"Amazing work! You've given me everything I need to create a compelling landing page for Friend of the Pod. Now you have two options:\\\",\\n  \\\"examples\\\": [\\n    \\\"Personalize the design (optional): Upload your logo, pick brand colors, add social links, or choose specific images. Check out the Brand Personalization panel on the left.\\\",\\n    \\\"Build right away: Skip personalization for now and hit 'Build My Site' to see your page. You can always customize later!\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"What sounds good to you?\\\"\\n}\\n```\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":5147,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":145,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
